planted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert Cockram was born in 1485, in Cullompton, Devon, England, United Kingdom, his father, George Cockram, was 27 and his mother, Lady Edith West, was 20. He married Betty Lantrip in 1505, in Dorset, England, United Kingdom. He died in 1525, in Cullompton, Devon, England, at the age of 40, and was buried in Devon, England."},"et":{"1485–1525":"1485–1525","1458–1510":"1458–1510","1479–1558":"1479–1558","1480–1589":"1480–1589","1484–1514":"1484–1514","1488–1514":"1488–1514","1505–1531":"1505–1531","1510–1589":"1510–1589","1465–1515":"1465–1515","1484":"1484","1480":"1480","1514":"1514","1525":"1525","1558":"1558","1458":"1458","1479":"1479","1589":"1589","1510":"1510","1488":"1488","1465":"1465","1531":"1531","1485":"1485","1505":"1505","1515":"1515","Nymet Epi., Devon, England":"Devon, England","Collumpton, Devon, England":"Collumpton MM, Devon, England","Devon, England, United Kingdom":"Devon, England","Cullompton, Devon, England":"Cullompton, Devon, England","Honiton, Devon, England":"Honiton, Devon, England","Dorset, England":"Dorset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Devon, England":"Devon, England","Poxwell, Dorset, England":"Poxwell, Dorset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1485–1525":"1485–1525","1458–1510":"1458–1510","1479–1558":"1479–1558","1480–1589":"1480–1589","1484–1514":"1484–1514","1488–1514":"1488–1514","1505–1531":"1505–1531","1510–1589":"1510–1589","1465–1515":"1465–1515","1484":"1484","1480":"1480","1514":"15